# Naming Convention Rules

## Purpose

Standardized naming ensures LLM can correctly reference entities and components.

## Entity Naming

### Format
```
{type}_{descriptor}_{number}
```

### Examples
| Entity | Name | Rationale |
|--------|------|-----------|
| Wall | `wall_south_001` | Type + location + ID |
| Door | `door_entrance_001` | Type + function + ID |
| Window | `window_living_001` | Type + room + ID |
| Sofa | `sofa_living_001` | Type + room + ID |
| Table | `table_dining_001` | Type + room + ID |

## Component Naming

### Furniture
```
{type}_{style}_{material}_{number}
```

Examples:
- `sofa_modern_grey_001`
- `chair_vintage_oak_001`
- `table_dining_oak_1400_001`

### Lighting
```
{type}_{location}_{number}
```

Examples:
- `lamp_floor_living_001`
- `chandelier_dining_001`
- `spotlight_ceiling_kitchen_001`

## Layer Names

| Layer | Contents |
|-------|----------|
| `Walls` | Exterior and interior walls |
| `Floors` | Floor surfaces |
| `Ceilings` | Ceiling surfaces |
| `Furniture` | All furniture components |
| `Fixtures` | Bathroom, kitchen fixtures |
| `Lighting` | Light fixtures and sources |
| `Electrical` | Outlets, switches |
| `Text` | Labels, annotations |

## Semantic Position Keys

| Key Pattern | Example |
|-------------|---------|
| `{room}_{feature}_center` | `living_room_center` |
| `{furniture}_center` | `dining_table_center` |
| `{furniture}_left` | `sofa_left_edge` |
| `{furniture}_front` | `bed_headboard` |

## Design Model IDs

### Format
```
{prefix}_{type}_{number}
```

| Prefix | Type | Example |
|--------|------|---------|
| `space_` | Space | `space_living_room_001` |
| `comp_` | Component | `comp_sofa_001` |
| `mat_` | Material | `mat_oak_wood` |
| `scene_` | Scene/Camera | `scene_birdseye_001` |

## LLM Usage

When LLM needs to reference an entity:
1. Look up in design_model.json
2. Use exact name as key
3. Never guess entity IDs

When LLM creates entity:
1. Generate name using convention above
2. Record in design_model.json
3. Return name to user in confirmation
